ar High Scale Kurn, so try to get people who are of those classes and need these bits and you already have half the people you need. <br>Two good groups should be enough for the hole. The only real difficult bit is gettng through the city part cause you can get a lot of adds. You should aim to get at least one good chanter and a couple of clerics. Some mobs are hard to mez, so a couple of tanks helps to split tank extras. You slowing mobs and as backup healer will help a lot too.<br>I would suggest making up a first level halfling rogue of brell and sneaking and hiding all the way down to Kirn and learn the way off by heart and take note of what mobs are where. Be warned a lot of golems can come when you start to pull the city.<br>There are a couple of great maps around of the hole that show all the mobs and their pathing. At first they are a bit hard to piece together, but after you have run your little rogue around they all make sense.<br>Good luck. <p><img src="http://users.bigpond.net.au/samirsk/hand.jpg" border="0"><Br> <a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=9095 target="web">Samir</a><Br> Proud Member of The Hand</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#013B3D><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub61.ezboard.com/uskeeth.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Skeeth</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_bluespot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 12<br> <font color=#FFFF00>(4/17/02 11:22:37 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub61.ezboard.com/fthehand90785frm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=405.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Epic questions. Since I know you guys have done.</span><hr size=1> Thanks guys<br> <p><img src= "http://www.battletechcentral.nu/Eqchars.jpg" >Skeeth Moonshadow 52 Shaman // Melodar Tunetwist 46 Bard // Marinius Blade